The paper deals with private information retrieval (PIR) over a distributed storage system, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The use of MDS codes for storage and retrieval also relates to database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses privacy and security concerns, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper presents a linear capacity-achieving scheme, which involves coding theory (cs.CC).
